snippet.title: Five reasons you should watch Tomb Raider
snippet.description:
For 22 years, ever since the first Tomb Raider game was released, we’ve know Lara Croft as an intrepid adventurer who can escape great danger, plunder ancient treasures and do a really impressive back-flip-while-shooting-guns maneuver. She was not always this way. When we first meet Lara Croft in Tomb Raider, her first movie in 15 years, she is actually not a tomb raider. She’s a young woman whose father disappeared while trying to solve an ancient mystery and left her alone. She’s now trying to make her way in the world, refusing to accept her father’s vast fortune because inheriting it would mean admitting he is dead. The film follows the perilous adventure that turned Lara into the hero we know.

snippet.title: Big Shaq's Alternative Queen's Speech
snippet.description:
Man’s Not Hot – he’s only taken off his jacket because his mum told him. Why? Because Big Shaq, man of the moment, is here to deliver his adoring public an alternative Queen’s Speech, especially for NME.

Who better to sum up the year that was 2017? Hard to believe it was only in August that the rapper (aka comedian Michael Dapaah) delivered his infamous freestyle on Charlie Sloth’s ‘Fire in the Booth’ YouTube show. One viral hit later, and he released an official version of ‘Man’s Not Hot’, which has been streamed more than 74 million streams on Spotify, while more than 100 million people have watched the (very glamorous) video.

A truly modern superstar, then. So we cut to Buckingham Palace, where Big Shaq – looking festive as fuck in his highly excellent ‘Man’s Not Hot’ Christmas jumper – has blagged his way beside the Christmas tree and has some words of wisdom on the high and lows of the past 12 months. Nothing but respect for my Monarch.


He shouts out Harry and Meghan, Cheryl and Harry (?), while Donald Trump receives a deadpan look of disapproval that would make his hair stand on end. Merry Christmas, one and all. Have a piping hot 2018.

snippet.title: NME’s 2017 blooper reel, starring Marilyn Manson, Skepta and Liam Gallagher
snippet.description:
Rock stars - they're just like us!

Everyone makes mistakes, even your favourite musicians. This year we here at NME have interviewed hundreds of the biggest names in the world and it’s not always gone to plan. Luckily for us though, we decided to save all the silliest moments and make a blooper reel of our fave fuck-ups, from Skepta mistaking a bottle of Jameson for a microphone at the NME Awards and Marilyn Manson crawling across a table during our interview in Berlin to Liam Gallagher deciding he quite fancies himself as a lady after being show his FaceApp face swap pics and Cillian Murphy not knowing what a meme is. We told him, don’t worry.

Our reel is packed full of appearances from loads of other legends, including Sam Smith, Louis Theroux, Matty Healy – who videobombs Skepta, Ryan Adams, Wiley and the Mayor London Sadiq Khan, Dan from Bastille, Craig David, Chino from Deftones, Hanson – yes, that Hanson. We love them, one and all – thanks for doing something silly in front of Team NME in 2017. Now roll on 2018 and another year of madness, mayhem and mistaking bottles of booze for audio recording devices.
